Past tense

    I missed Technical Session last week.
    I worked for 9 Hours Yesterday.
    I washing the dishes when the phone rang.
    Wash she reading the book when they came?
    It was heavy raining yesterday Evening
    
    
Present tense
  
    We work hard Everyday
    Arun eats a Banana
    They watch television regularly.
    London is a large city
    Open the packet and pour the contents into hot water.
    
    
Future tense

    I will do this tomorrow.
    I will miss you when you move to another country.
    I will have finished my report by 10.
    I am going to finish my work soon.
    We will be back for dinner.


     
        
    
